  "statement": {
    "markdown": "You are given two groups of integers. The first group represents the greed factor of each child, where the i‑th integer g[i] denotes the minimum size of a cookie that the i‑th child will be satisfied with. The second group represents the sizes of available cookies, where the j‑th integer s[j] denotes the size of the j‑th cookie.\n\nEach child can receive at most one cookie, and each cookie can be given to at most one child. A child is content if the size of the cookie it receives is greater than or equal to its greed factor. Your task is to determine the maximum number of content children you can achieve by distributing the cookies optimally.\n\n**Input Format**\n- The first line contains an integer `n`, the number of children.\n- The second line contains `n` space‑separated integers `g[1] … g[n]`, the greed factors of the children.\n- The third line contains an integer `m`, the number of cookies.\n- The fourth line contains `m` space‑separated integers `s[1] … s[m]`, the sizes of the cookies.\n\n**Output Format**\n- Print a single integer, the maximum number of content children.\n\n**Notes**\n- You may assign the cookies in any order.\n- If a child cannot be satisfied with any remaining cookie, it remains unsatisfied.\n- The optimal strategy is to sort both arrays and use a two‑pointer greedy approach.\n\n**Constraints**\n- `1 ≤ n ≤ 100000`\n- `1 ≤ m ≤ 100000`\n- `1 ≤ g[i] ≤ 1000000000`\n- `1 ≤ s[j] ≤ 1000000000`\n\n**Examples**\n\n**Example 1**\nInput:\n3\n1 2 3\n2\n1 1\nOutput:\n1\nExplanation:\nOnly one child (with greed factor 1) can receive a cookie of size 1. The other two children cannot be satisfied.\n\n**Example 2**\nInput:\n4\n1 2 3 4\n4\n2 3 4 5\nOutput:\n4\nExplanation:\nAll children can be satisfied: assign cookie size 2 to child 1, 3 to child 2, 4 to child 3, and 5 to child 4.",
    "inputFormat": "n\ng[1] g[2] ... g[n]\nm\ns[1] s[2] ... s[m]",
    "outputFormat": "maxContentChildren",
    "notes": "The greedy two‑pointer method works because giving the smallest possible cookie that satisfies a child leaves larger cookies for children with larger greed factors.",
